The key is the ISRC code. Every distributor generates one for each song on a release. The only time an ISRC code should be different for the same song is if there's some creative difference (i.e., a new master). So, if the master sound recording is the same between releases, then it counts as one song. Source: I'm a musician who has distributed music before.
